      public Vector()
      Create a new, neutral vector.

    • Vector

      public Vector(int direction, double length)
      Create a vector with given direction and length. The direction should be in the range [0..359], where 0 is EAST, and degrees increase clockwise.

    • Vector

      public Vector(double dx, double dy)
      Create a vector by specifying the x and y offsets from start to end points.

    • Vector

      public Vector(double x0, double x1, boolean polar)
      Create a vector with given direction and length or by specifying the x and y offsets from start to end points. In the case of polar coordinates, the direction should be in the range [0..360[ , where 0 is EAST, and degrees increase clockwise.
